<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-03-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-03-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="232" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d232">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Chargé <persName type="to">Fletcher</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-03-01"><hi rend="italic">March 1,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Wilson directs Mr. Fletcher to send, if possible, copy of text of
                            China’s alleged promise, made in 1899, not to build railways north of
                            Peking without consulting Russia.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>